  <div class="container">
    <div class="full-width">
      <h2>Full-Bleed Content</h2>
      <p>As you can see, the background of this section extends to the ends of the screen. This is done by simply adding a <code>div</code> with class <code>.full-bleed</code> around a <code>.container</code> element. Otherwise, you follow the rules with wrapping things inside the appropriate grid wrappers, such as <code>.full-width</code> and <code>.row></code>, etc.</p>
      <p>All types of gridded content (shown below) can be used inside of full-bleed areas without any tweaks needed.</p>
    </div> <!-- end: .full-width -->
  </div> <!-- end: .container -->
</div> <!-- end: .full-bleed -->

